  "original_title": "\u0bb9\u0bc6\u0bb2\u0bcd\u0bae\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bc8 \u0bb5\u0bc0\u0b9a\u0bbf\u0baf \u0b85\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bbf \u0b86\u0baf\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0b9f\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0b95\u0bc8\u0ba4\u0bc1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "The officer who threw the helmet was arrested with a weapon",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Police said that a police officer who supported the popular protest held on Saturday (09) demanding the resignation of the President and Prime Minister, was arrested when he entered the Presidential Palace in the Fort, Colombo early this morning (11) with a sharp weapon.",
        "The officer had shown support by throwing his turban at Maharagama Nagar to the protestors who were coming from High Level Road.",
        "Superintendent of Police and Police Media Spokesman Nihal Talduwa said that he was on duty at the Police Traffic Division in Homagama, Magamana.",
        "The spokesperson said that after the military officials became suspicious of the man who was wearing police uniform and sandals, a sharp weapon was found during a search of him.",
        "A weapon measuring 10 inches long and 2 inches wide was seized from him and he has been handed over to Fort Police Station for further investigations, it said."
      ],
